commentPostTextItems.html: India are all out for a paltry 133 chasing 201 in 47 overs
A 67n run loss is the result and India are still in search of a win in this tournament
PIndia are languishing at the bottom of the points table with 0 points. Sri Lanka have 6 points from 3 matches. New Zealand have four points from 3 matches
It's a rather depressing day for Indian cricket, unable to chgase 201 runs
Virender Sehwag, yet another experiment as an opener made 33, the top score of the indian innings
The Kiwi's of course have been in absolutely cracking touch today
Apart from putting on as many runs as possible in less than perfect batting conditions, they defended their low score well
In the early overs when India seemed to hvae a glimmer of hope the New Zelanaders fielded in amanner that would have made any captain proud - like cornered Tigers, to quote Imran Khan from 1992
The Indians found the going tough as one by one their batsmen failed to get going
To top it all, the run outs kept coming as well and there seemed to be nothing the New Zealanders could do wrong
At the end of the day Harris had figures of 7-3-9-2, Vettori 10-0-33-1, Nash 7.4-0-25-1 and so on... everyone was tidy
The end result - a comprehensive New Zealand win!
That's all we have for you from the R Premadasa Stadium in Colombo
Join us again on Saturday, 27 July for the next clash. That will start at at 1000 local time, 0400GMT, please be there to see if there is any change of fortunes in this tournament!
So far it has been Sri Lanka and New Zealand all the way
This was a cracker of a match and no doubt you would have something to say about it, whatever it is send your mail to comms@cricinfo.com If you tell us what you want we can always improve!
It was a pleasure bringing you this match, we hope the next one we bring you is more competitive!
Till the next match, a very good evening to you all
